This paper deals with algorithms for recurrent neural networks, which are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper discusses the relationship between two specific algorithms, Recurrent Backpropagation and Equilibrium Propagation, which are used for error computation and relaxation, respectively. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). However, the paper also touches upon topics related to machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), control systems (cs.SY), and computer vision (cs.CV).
